onvention, causing potential user confusion.\n- **Fix**: Removed `-h` short flag; users can still use `--host` with long form.\n\n### Issues Intentionally NOT Changed\n\n**Hard Dependencies (fastapi/uvicorn)**: Preserved as hard dependencies per the diff context. The finding suggested optionality, but the implementation treats HTTP API as a core feature. This is reasonable if: (1) the API is intended to be primary, or (2) documentation clarifies installation: `pip install factory` includes API server. If future needs change, moving to `[project.optional-dependencies]` with name `'api'` is straightforward.\n\n**Missing Content-Negotiation Tests**: Deferred as Info/Low-confidence finding. Current `test_server.py` provides sufficient baseline coverage for a simple healthcheck endpoint. Accept header and charset variants can be added when API expands beyond `/hello`.\n\n### Test Coverage Now Includes\n- ✅ Valid port ranges (0–65535) actually invoke uvicorn\n- ✅ Invalid ports rejected before uvicorn invocation\n- ✅ Host and port parameters correctly passed to uvicorn\n- ✅ OSError handling for port conflicts\n- ✅ Generic exception handling for startup failures\n- ✅ Default host/port validation\n- ✅ Endpoint JSON response, content-type, method rejection (405), and 404 handling\n\n### Convergence\nAll critical and warning-level issues are now resolved. The code follows established patterns (error handling mirrors slack-listen), maintains type safety (Pydantic models), and is properly testable (mocked uvicorn allows deterministic CLI tests).",
