        "body": "**Missing error handling for uvicorn.run() startup failures**\n\nThe serve() function calls uvicorn.run(server_app, host=host, port=port) without any try/except or error handling. uvicorn.run() can raise multiple exceptions at runtime: (1) OSError when port is already in use or binding fails (permission denied, address already in use); (2) socket.error for network binding failures; (3) ValueError for invalid host/port combinations; (4) Other exceptions from the FastAPI application. Without error handling, users see raw Python tracebacks instead of actionable error messages. Contrast with the slack-listen command (lines 1077-1084) which explicitly handles ImportError for optional dependencies with helpful messages.\n\nRaised by: claude-code\n\nSuggested fix: Wrap uvicorn.run() in try/except: try:\\n    uvicorn.run(server_app, host=host, port=port)\\nexcept OSError as e:\\n    typer.echo(f\"Failed to bind to {host}:{port}: {e}\", err=True)\\n    raise typer.Exit(1)\\nexcept Exception as e:\\n    typer.echo(f\"Server startup failed: {e}\", err=True)\\n    raise typer.Exit(1)",
