        "body": "**CLI tests skip actual uvicorn.run() execution via --help flag**\n\nAll tests in test_cli_serve.py use the --help flag to verify the command exists and accepts parameters, but this prevents uvicorn.run() from ever being invoked. The --help flag causes typer to display help text and exit before reaching line 966 in cli.py where uvicorn.run(server_app, host=host, port=port) executes. This means: (1) uvicorn startup is never tested; (2) server configuration (host/port binding) is never verified; (3) integration between FastAPI app and uvicorn is untested; (4) runtime errors from uvicorn are never caught by tests. Tests that should validate edge cases (port 0, port 65535) are rendered meaningless because they also use --help to skip execution.\n\nRaised by: claude-code\n\nSuggested fix: Replace test_serve_with_port_zero() and test_serve_with_port_65535() to test without --help and mock uvicorn.run(). Alternatively, add a pytest fixture that monkey-patches uvicorn.run to verify it's called with correct arguments: @patch('factory.cli.uvicorn.run') def test_serve_actually_invokes_uvicorn(mock_run): result = runner.invoke(app, ['serve', '--host', '0.0.0.0', '--port', '5000']); mock_run.assert_called_once_with(server_app, host='0.0.0.0', port=5000)",
